//Medial collateral ligaments


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Medial collateral ligaments' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Sprain, grade 1 Injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial tear, grade 2 injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Complete tear, grade 3 injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Bursitis between deep and middle layer' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Sprain, grade 1 Injury' radio button
Then 'Bursitis between deep and middle layer' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Partial tear, grade 2 injury' radio button
Then 'Rupture superficial layer' radio button is enabled
And 'Rupture deep layer' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then 'Dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Complete tear, grade 3 injury' radio button
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then 'Dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Bursitis between deep and middle layer' radio button
Then 'Sprain, grade 1 Injury' checkbox is enabled
